ra of profound economic and social transformation. All of the men Rico discusses—from the well known, including Theodore Roosevelt and Buffalo Bill Cody, to the comparatively obscure, such as English cattle rancher Moreton Frewen—envisioned the American West as a global space into which redemptive narratives of heroic upper-class masculinity could be written.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aBritishzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 0aFrontier and pioneer lifezWest (U.S.). 0aMasculinityzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aMasculinityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aUpper classzGreat BritainxHistoryy19th century. 0aUpper classzWest (U.S.)xHistoryy19th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 19th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z97831105379940 cprintz978030013606740uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030019625240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300196252423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300196252/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY